CHIP Clonal Hematopoiesis of Indeterminate Potential.

Compared to a previously published EWAS of CHIP12 (N = 3273, 228 CHIP cases), the present study has a substantially larger sample size (N = 8196, 462 CHIP cases), including all the samples from the previous study. With the larger sample size of the present study, we identified 6687, 3524, and 4678 novel CpGs significantly associated with any CHIP and with the top two CHIP driver genes DNMT3A and TET2. Of the CpG sites identified from the previous EWAS study at P < 1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
